-- Petron Rises Most in 4 Weeks in Manila on Energy Expansion Plan
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-03-28T07:21:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/petron-rises-most-in-4-weeks-in-manila-on-energy-expansion-plan.html
Petron Corp. (PCOR)  climbed the most in
four weeks in Manila trading after President Eric Recto said the
company plans to further invest in power generation.  The stock rose 2.6 percent to 10.14 pesos as of 3:05 p.m.
local time, poised for the sharpest gain since Feb. 28. The
benchmark Philippine Stock Exchange Index decreased 0.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
